label.value: Periodontal Insert Dosage Form

value.value: Solid single-dose preparation consisting of a medicated insert to be placed within the tooth socket/periodontal membrane. The biodegradable insert is a sheet which slowly releases active substance(s).

label.value: Periodontal Powder Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended for administration within the tooth socket/periodontal membrane.

label.value: Periosseous Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of a medicinal product on or around the bone

label.value: Peritumoral Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of a medicinal product directly into the region surrounding a tumor.

label.value: Pessary Dosage Form

value.value: Solid, single-dose preparation usually prepared by molding, of various shapes, usually ovoid, with a volume and consistency suitable for insertion into the vagina to obtain a local effect. It contains one or more active substances dispersed or dissolved in a suitable basis that may be soluble or dispersible in water or may melt at body temperature.

label.value: Pessary Dosage Unit

value.value: A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single discrete entity where the pharmaceutical dose form is a type of pessary.

label.value: Pillule Dosage Unit

value.value: A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single discrete entity where the pharmaceutical dose form is a type of pillule.

label.value: Pillule Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation for homeopathic use, obtained from sucrose, lactose or other suitable excipients. Pillules may be prepared by impregnation of preformed pillules with a dilution or dilutions of homeopathic stocks or by progressive addition of these excipients and the addition of a dilution or dilutions of homeopathic stocks. Pillules are intended for oral or sublingual use.

label.value: Pillules in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of pillules presented in a single-dose container.

label.value: PBB/Ld Mouse
Pipette Dosage Unit

value.value: A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single pipette administration device.

label.value: Plaster Dosing Unit

value.value: A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single discrete entity where the pharmaceutical dose form is a type of plaster.

label.value: Plaster for Provocation Test Dosage Form

value.value: Solid flexible preparation containing an allergen product intended for provocation testing by application to the skin.

label.value: Plug Dosing Unit

value.value: A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single discrete entity where the pharmaceutical dose form is a type of plug.

label.value: Posterior Juxtascleral Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of a medicinal product beneath the sub-tenon membrane of the sclera (i.e. in the episcleral space), adjacent to the macula.

label.value: Pouch Dosage Form
Pour-on Container

value.value: Container with built-in applicator for pouring-on use.

label.value: Pour-on Emulsion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for pour-on use for the prevention and treatment of ectoparasitic and/or endoparasitic infestations of animals. Pour-on emulsions are applied in volumes that are usually greater than 5 mL.

label.value: Pour-on Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for pour-on use for the prevention and treatment of ectoparasitic and/or endoparasitic infestations of animals. Pour-on solutions are applied in volumes that are usually greater than 5 mL.

label.value: Pour-on Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a suspension intended for pour-on use for the prevention and treatment of ectoparasitic and/or endoparasitic infestations of animals. Pour-on suspensions are applied in volumes that are usually greater than 5 mL.

label.value: VY/Wf-a^m/a Male, Oakridge, 1965, F5
Pour-on Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of a veterinary medicinal product by pouring onto the dorsal midline of the animal or to the top of the head and around the base of the horns.

label.value: Powder and Gel for Gel Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and gel intended for the preparation of a gel (for cutaneous use) by mixing the powder in the gel. The powder contains active ingredient(s); the gel does not contain active ingredient(s).

label.value: Powder and Solution for Beehive Dispersion Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solution, both of which contain active ingredient(s), intended for the preparation of a bee-hive dispersion by mixing the powder with the solution.

label.value: Powder and Solution for Beehive Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solution, both of which contain active ingredient(s), intended for the preparation of a bee-hive solution by dissolving the powder in the solution.

label.value: Powder and Solution for Dental Cement Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solution, both containing active substance(s), intended for the preparation of a dental cement by mixing the powder and the solution.

label.value: Powder and Solution for Solution for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solution, both containing active substance(s), intended for the preparation of a solution for injection by dissolving the powder in the solution.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Concentrate for Solution for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a concentrate for solution for infusion by dissolving the powder in the solvent; the resulting concentrate for solution for infusion must subsequently be diluted before administration as a solution for infusion.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Topical Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of a cutaneous solution by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Dental Gel Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of a dental gel by mixing the powder and the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Emulsion for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of an emulsion for injection by mixing the powder and the solvent.

label.value: AM Mouse
Powder and Solvent for Endocervical Gel Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of an endocervical gel by mixing the powder and the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Endosinusial Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of an endosinusial solution by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Epilesional Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of an epilesional solution by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Gingival Gel Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of a gingival gel by mixing the powder and the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Implantation Paste Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of an implantation paste by dispersing the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Intraocular Instillation Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of an intraocular instillation solution by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Intravesical Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of an intravesical solution by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Intravesical Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of an intravesical suspension by dispersing the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Nebulizer Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of a nebulizer solution by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Oral Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of an oral solution by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: VY/Wf-A^vy/aF12, GL Wolff, Natl Ctr Toxicol Res
Powder and Solvent for Oral Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and solvent intended for the preparation of an oral suspension by dispersing the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Prolonged-Release Suspension for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a prolonged-release suspension for injection by dispersing the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Prolonged-Release Suspension for Injection in Pre-filled Pen Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a powder and solvent for prolonged-release suspension for injection presented in a pre-filled pen. The powder and solvent are contained in different compartments of the pre-filled pen, which contains all of the components necessary to prepare the prolonged-release suspension for injection.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Prolonged-Release Suspension for Injection in Pre-filled Syringe Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a powder and solvent for prolonged-release suspension for injection presented in a pre-filled syringe. The powder and solvent are contained in different compartments of the pre-filled syringe, which contains all of the components necessary to prepare the prolonged-release suspension for injection.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Sealant Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a sealant by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Solution for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a solution for infusion by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Powder and Solvent for Solution for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a solution for injection by dissolving the powder in the solvent.
